Default the menu bar (File / Edit / View / …) to visible.

Firefox ships the menu bar with `autohide="true"` so it's only visible
while Alt is held. Gjoa wants it visible by default — discoverable
navigation, no chord required.

Users can still hide it via View > Toolbars > Menu Bar (which toggles
the autohide attribute, persisted to localstore).

diff --git a/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml b/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml
--- a/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml
+++ b/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml
@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@
            class="browser-toolbar chromeclass-menubar browser-titlebar"
            customizable="true"
            mode="icons"
-           autohide="true"
+           autohide="false"
            context="toolbar-context-menu">
     <toolbaritem id="menubar-items" align="center">
 # The entire main menubar is placed into browser-menubar.inc, so that it can be
